						               													<description>Chessnuts is a collection of seven four-player Chess variants and one four-player Checkers variant. They are all played on an 8x8 board with four 2x8 wings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In five of the Chess variants each player plays individually. The games differ in their victory conditions - in three the object is to be the last player with a king, in the other two captured and remaining pieces are scoring using a points system - the game-ending condition, and the effects of losing one's king.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The other two Chess variants are played in partnerships; in one the players sit opposite each other and in the other they sit adjacent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All the games are named after types of nut, e.g. the adjacent partners game is called Hazelnut.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The components are a roll-up vinyl board and four sets of plastic pieces, all packaged in a tube.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
